{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"In the spirit of Jacques Cousteau, who said,"},{"time":3000,"text":"\"People protect what they love,\""},{"time":5000,"text":"I want to share with you today what I love most in the ocean,"},{"time":8000,"text":"and that's the incredible number and variety"},{"time":11000,"text":"of animals in it that make light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14000,"text":"My addiction began with this strange looking diving suit called Wasp;"},{"time":17000,"text":"that's not an acronym -- just somebody thought it looked like the insect."},{"time":20000,"text":"It was actually developed for use by the offshore oil industry"},{"time":23000,"text":"for diving on oil rigs down to a depth of 2,000 feet."},{"time":26000,"text":"Right after I completed my Ph.D.,"},{"time":28000,"text":"I was lucky enough to be included with a group of scientists"},{"time":31000,"text":"that was using it for the first time"},{"time":33000,"text":"as a tool for ocean exploration."},{"time":35000,"text":"We trained in a tank in Port Hueneme,"},{"time":37000,"text":"and then my first open ocean dive"},{"time":39000,"text":"was in Santa Barbara Channel."},{"time":41000,"text":"It was an evening dive."},{"time":43000,"text":"I went down to a depth of 880 feet"},{"time":46000,"text":"and turned out the lights."},{"time":48000,"text":"And the reason I turned out the lights is because I knew I would see"},{"time":50000,"text":"this phenomenon of animals making light"},{"time":52000,"text":"called bioluminescence."},{"time":54000,"text":"But I was totally unprepared"},{"time":56000,"text":"for how much there was"},{"time":58000,"text":"and how spectacular it was."},{"time":61000,"text":"I saw chains of jellyfish called siphonophores"},{"time":64000,"text":"that were longer than this room,"},{"time":66000,"text":"pumping out so much light"},{"time":68000,"text":"that I could read the dials and gauges"},{"time":70000,"text":"inside the suit without a flashlight;"},{"time":72000,"text":"and puffs and billows"},{"time":74000,"text":"of what looked like luminous blue smoke;"},{"time":77000,"text":"and explosions of sparks"},{"time":79000,"text":"that would swirl up out of the thrusters --"},{"time":81000,"text":"just like when you throw a log on a campfire and the embers swirl up off the campfire,"},{"time":84000,"text":"but these were icy, blue embers."},{"time":86000,"text":"It was breathtaking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"Now, usually if people are familiar with bioluminescence at all,"},{"time":91000,"text":"it's these guys; it's fireflies."},{"time":93000,"text":"And there are a few other land-dwellers that can make light --"},{"time":95000,"text":"some insects, earthworms, fungi --"},{"time":97000,"text":"but in general, on land, it's really rare."},{"time":100000,"text":"In the ocean, it's the rule"},{"time":102000,"text":"rather than the exception."},{"time":104000,"text":"If I go out in the open ocean environment,"},{"time":106000,"text":"virtually anywhere in the world,"},{"time":108000,"text":"and I drag a net from 3,000 feet to the surface,"},{"time":111000,"text":"most of the animals --"},{"time":113000,"text":"in fact, in many places, 80 to 90 percent"},{"time":115000,"text":"of the animals that I bring up in that net --"},{"time":118000,"text":"make light."},{"time":120000,"text":"This makes for some pretty spectacular light shows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"Now I want to share with you a little video"},{"time":125000,"text":"that I shot from a submersible."},{"time":127000,"text":"I first developed this technique working from a little"},{"time":129000,"text":"single-person submersible called Deep Rover"},{"time":132000,"text":"and then adapted it for use on the Johnson Sea-Link,"},{"time":134000,"text":"which you see here."},{"time":136000,"text":"So, mounted in front of the observation sphere,"},{"time":138000,"text":"there's a a three-foot diameter hoop"},{"time":141000,"text":"with a screen stretched across it."},{"time":143000,"text":"And inside the sphere with me is an intensified camera"},{"time":145000,"text":"that's about as sensitive as a fully dark-adapted human eye,"},{"time":148000,"text":"albeit a little fuzzy."},{"time":150000,"text":"So you turn on the camera, turn out the lights."},{"time":152000,"text":"That sparkle you're seeing is not luminescence,"},{"time":154000,"text":"that's just electronic noise"},{"time":156000,"text":"on these super intensified cameras."},{"time":158000,"text":"You don't see luminescence until the submersible"},{"time":160000,"text":"begins to move forward through the water,"},{"time":162000,"text":"but as it does, animals bumping into the screen"},{"time":164000,"text":"are stimulated to bioluminesce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"Now, when I was first doing this,"},{"time":168000,"text":"all I was trying to do was count the numbers of sources."},{"time":170000,"text":"I knew my forward speed, I knew the area,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and so I could figure out how many hundreds of sources"},{"time":174000,"text":"there were per cubic meter."},{"time":176000,"text":"But I started to realize that I could actually identify animals"},{"time":178000,"text":"by the type of flashes they produced."},{"time":180000,"text":"And so, here, in the Gulf of Maine"},{"time":183000,"text":"at 740 feet,"},{"time":185000,"text":"I can name pretty much everything you're seeing there to the species level."},{"time":188000,"text":"Like those big explosions, sparks,"},{"time":190000,"text":"are from a little comb jelly,"},{"time":192000,"text":"and there's krill and other kinds of crustaceans,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and jellyfish."},{"time":197000,"text":"There was another one of those comb jellies."},{"time":199000,"text":"And so I've worked with computer image analysis engineers"},{"time":202000,"text":"to develop automatic recognition systems"},{"time":205000,"text":"that can identify these animals"},{"time":207000,"text":"and then extract the XYZ coordinate of the initial impact point."},{"time":210000,"text":"And we can then do the kinds of things that ecologists do on land,"},{"time":213000,"text":"and do nearest neighbor distances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216000,"text":"But you don't always have to go down to the depths of the ocean"},{"time":218000,"text":"to see a light show like this."},{"time":220000,"text":"You can actually see it in surface waters."},{"time":222000,"text":"This is some shot, by Dr. Mike Latz at Scripps Institution,"},{"time":225000,"text":"of a dolphin swimming through bioluminescent plankton."},{"time":227000,"text":"And this isn't someplace exotic"},{"time":229000,"text":"like one of the bioluminescent bays in Puerto Rico,"},{"time":232000,"text":"this was actually shot in San Diego Harbor."},{"time":234000,"text":"And sometimes you can see it even closer than that,"},{"time":237000,"text":"because the heads on ships --"},{"time":239000,"text":"that's toilets, for any land lovers that are listening --"},{"time":242000,"text":"are flushed with unfiltered seawater"},{"time":245000,"text":"that often has bioluminescent plankton in it."},{"time":247000,"text":"So, if you stagger into the head late at night"},{"time":249000,"text":"and you're so toilet-hugging sick"},{"time":251000,"text":"that you forget to turn on the light,"},{"time":253000,"text":"you may think that you're having a religious experience. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"So, how does a living creature make light?"},{"time":258000,"text":"Well, that was the question that 19th century"},{"time":260000,"text":"French physiologist Raphael Dubois,"},{"time":262000,"text":"asked about this bioluminescent clam."},{"time":264000,"text":"He ground it up and he managed to get out a couple of chemicals;"},{"time":267000,"text":"one, the enzyme, he called luciferase;"},{"time":270000,"text":"the substrate, he called luciferin"},{"time":272000,"text":"after Lucifer the Lightbearer."},{"time":274000,"text":"That terminology has stuck, but it doesn't actually refer to specific chemicals"},{"time":277000,"text":"because these chemicals come in a lot of different shapes and forms."},{"time":280000,"text":"In fact, most of the people"},{"time":282000,"text":"studying bioluminescence today"},{"time":284000,"text":"are focused on the chemistry, because these chemicals"},{"time":286000,"text":"have proved so incredibly valuable"},{"time":288000,"text":"for developing antibacterial agents,"},{"time":291000,"text":"cancer fighting drugs,"},{"time":293000,"text":"testing for the presence of life on Mars,"},{"time":295000,"text":"detecting pollutants in our waters --"},{"time":297000,"text":"which is how we use it at ORCA."},{"time":299000,"text":"In 2008,"},{"time":301000,"text":"the Nobel Prize in Chemistry"},{"time":303000,"text":"was awarded for work done"},{"time":305000,"text":"on a molecule called green fluorescent protein"},{"time":307000,"text":"that was isolated from the bioluminescent chemistry"},{"time":310000,"text":"of a jellyfish,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and it's been equated to the invention of the microscope,"},{"time":314000,"text":"in terms of the impact that it has had"},{"time":317000,"text":"on cell biology and genetic engineering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"Another thing all these molecules are telling us"},{"time":322000,"text":"that, apparently, bioluminescence has evolved"},{"time":325000,"text":"at least 40 times, maybe as many as 50 separate times"},{"time":328000,"text":"in evolutionary history,"},{"time":330000,"text":"which is a clear indication"},{"time":332000,"text":"of how spectacularly important"},{"time":335000,"text":"this trait is for survival."},{"time":337000,"text":"So, what is it about bioluminescence"},{"time":339000,"text":"that's so important to so many animals?"},{"time":341000,"text":"Well, for animals that are trying to avoid predators"},{"time":344000,"text":"by staying in the darkness,"},{"time":347000,"text":"light can still be very useful"},{"time":349000,"text":"for the three basic things that animals have to do to survive:"},{"time":352000,"text":"and that's find food,"},{"time":354000,"text":"attract a mate and avoid being eaten."},{"time":356000,"text":"So, for example, this fish"},{"time":358000,"text":"has a built-in headlight behind its eye"},{"time":360000,"text":"that it can use for finding food"},{"time":362000,"text":"or attracting a mate."},{"time":364000,"text":"And then when it's not using it, it actually can roll it down into its head"},{"time":367000,"text":"just like the headlights on your Lamborghini."},{"time":370000,"text":"This fish actually has high beams."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"And this fish, which is one of my favorites,"},{"time":375000,"text":"has three headlights on each side of its head."},{"time":378000,"text":"Now, this one is blue,"},{"time":380000,"text":"and that's the color of most bioluminescence in the ocean"},{"time":382000,"text":"because evolution has selected"},{"time":384000,"text":"for the color that travels farthest through seawater"},{"time":386000,"text":"in order to optimize communication."},{"time":388000,"text":"So, most animals make blue light,"},{"time":390000,"text":"and most animals can only see blue light,"},{"time":393000,"text":"but this fish is a really fascinating exception"},{"time":395000,"text":"because it has two red light organs."},{"time":398000,"text":"And I have no idea why there's two,"},{"time":400000,"text":"and that's something I want to solve some day --"},{"time":402000,"text":"but not only can it see blue light,"},{"time":405000,"text":"but it can see red light."},{"time":407000,"text":"So it uses its red bioluminescence like a sniper's scope"},{"time":410000,"text":"to be able to sneak up on animals"},{"time":412000,"text":"that are blind to red light"},{"time":414000,"text":"and be able to see them without being seen."},{"time":416000,"text":"It's also got a little chin barbel here"},{"time":418000,"text":"with a blue luminescent lure on it"},{"time":420000,"text":"that it can use to attract prey from a long way off."},{"time":423000,"text":"And a lot of animals will use their bioluminescence as a lure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"This is another one of my favorite fish."},{"time":429000,"text":"This is a viperfish, and it's got a lure"},{"time":431000,"text":"on the end of a long fishing rod"},{"time":433000,"text":"that it arches in front of the toothy jaw"},{"time":435000,"text":"that gives the viperfish its name."},{"time":438000,"text":"The teeth on this fish are so long"},{"time":440000,"text":"that if they closed inside the mouth of the fish,"},{"time":442000,"text":"it would actually impale its own brain."},{"time":445000,"text":"So instead, it slides in grooves"},{"time":447000,"text":"on the outside of the head."},{"time":449000,"text":"This is a Christmas tree of a fish;"},{"time":451000,"text":"everything on this fish lights up,"},{"time":453000,"text":"it's not just that lure."},{"time":455000,"text":"It's got a built-in flashlight."},{"time":457000,"text":"It's got these jewel-like light organs on its belly"},{"time":459000,"text":"that it uses for a type of camouflage"},{"time":462000,"text":"that obliterates its shadow,"},{"time":465000,"text":"so when it's swimming around and there's a predator looking up from below,"},{"time":468000,"text":"it makes itself disappear."},{"time":470000,"text":"It's got light organs in the mouth,"},{"time":472000,"text":"it's got light organs in every single scale, in the fins,"},{"time":474000,"text":"in a mucus layer on the back and the belly,"},{"time":476000,"text":"all used for different things --"},{"time":478000,"text":"some of which we know about, some of which we don't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480000,"text":"And we know a little bit more about bioluminescence thanks to Pixar,"},{"time":483000,"text":"and I'm very grateful to Pixar for sharing"},{"time":485000,"text":"my favorite topic with so many people."},{"time":487000,"text":"I do wish, with their budget,"},{"time":489000,"text":"that they might have spent just a tiny bit more money"},{"time":492000,"text":"to pay a consulting fee to some poor, starving graduate student,"},{"time":495000,"text":"who could have told them that those are the eyes"},{"time":497000,"text":"of a fish that's been preserved in formalin."},{"time":500000,"text":"These are the eyes of a living anglerfish."},{"time":502000,"text":"So, she's got a lure that she sticks out"},{"time":504000,"text":"in front of this living mousetrap"},{"time":506000,"text":"of needle-sharp teeth"},{"time":508000,"text":"in order to attract in some unsuspecting prey."},{"time":511000,"text":"And this one has a lure"},{"time":513000,"text":"with all kinds of little interesting threads coming off it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516000,"text":"Now we used to think that the different shape of the lure"},{"time":519000,"text":"was to attract different types of prey,"},{"time":521000,"text":"but then stomach content analyses on these fish"},{"time":524000,"text":"done by scientists, or more likely their graduate students,"},{"time":527000,"text":"have revealed that"},{"time":529000,"text":"they all eat pretty much the same thing."},{"time":531000,"text":"So, now we believe that the different shape of the lure"},{"time":533000,"text":"is how the male recognizes the female"},{"time":535000,"text":"in the anglerfish world,"},{"time":537000,"text":"because many of these males"},{"time":539000,"text":"are what are known as dwarf males."},{"time":541000,"text":"This little guy"},{"time":543000,"text":"has no visible means of self-support."},{"time":546000,"text":"He has no lure for attracting food"},{"time":548000,"text":"and no teeth for eating it when it gets there."},{"time":550000,"text":"His only hope for existence on this planet"},{"time":553000,"text":"is as a gigolo. (Laughter)"},{"time":555000,"text":"He's got to find himself a babe"},{"time":557000,"text":"and then he's got to latch on for life."},{"time":560000,"text":"So this little guy"},{"time":562000,"text":"has found himself this babe,"},{"time":564000,"text":"and you will note that he's had the good sense"},{"time":566000,"text":"to attach himself in a way that he doesn't actually have to look at her."},{"time":569000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":571000,"text":"But he still knows a good thing when he sees it,"},{"time":573000,"text":"and so he seals the relationship with an eternal kiss."},{"time":576000,"text":"His flesh fuses with her flesh,"},{"time":578000,"text":"her bloodstream grows into his body,"},{"time":580000,"text":"and he becomes nothing more than a little sperm sac."},{"time":583000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":585000,"text":"Well, this is a deep-sea version of Women's Lib."},{"time":587000,"text":"She always knows where he is,"},{"time":589000,"text":"and she doesn't have to be monogamous,"},{"time":591000,"text":"because some of these females"},{"time":593000,"text":"come up with multiple males attached."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595000,"text":"So they can use it for finding food, for attracting mates."},{"time":598000,"text":"They use it a lot for defense, many different ways."},{"time":601000,"text":"A lot of them can release their luciferin or luferase in the water"},{"time":604000,"text":"just the way a squid or an octopus will release an ink cloud."},{"time":606000,"text":"This shrimp is actually"},{"time":608000,"text":"spewing light out of its mouth"},{"time":610000,"text":"like a fire breathing dragon"},{"time":612000,"text":"in order to blind or distract this viperfish"},{"time":614000,"text":"so that the shrimp can swim away into the darkness."},{"time":616000,"text":"And there are a lot of different animals that can do this:"},{"time":619000,"text":"There's jellyfish, there's squid,"},{"time":621000,"text":"there's a whole lot of different crustaceans,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"there's even fish that can do this."},{"time":625000,"text":"This fish is called the shining tubeshoulder"},{"time":628000,"text":"because it actually has a tube on its shoulder"},{"time":630000,"text":"that can squirt out light."},{"time":632000,"text":"And I was luck enough to capture one of these"},{"time":634000,"text":"when we were on a trawling expedition"},{"time":636000,"text":"off the northwest coast of Africa for \"Blue Planet,\""},{"time":639000,"text":"for the deep portion of \"Blue Planet.\""},{"time":641000,"text":"And we were using a special trawling net"},{"time":643000,"text":"that we were able to bring these animals up alive."},{"time":645000,"text":"So we captured one of these, and I brought it into the lab."},{"time":648000,"text":"So I'm holding it,"},{"time":650000,"text":"and I'm about to touch that tube on its shoulder,"},{"time":652000,"text":"and when I do, you'll see bioluminescence coming out."},{"time":656000,"text":"But to me, what's shocking"},{"time":658000,"text":"is not just the amount of light,"},{"time":660000,"text":"but the fact that it's not just luciferin and luciferase."},{"time":662000,"text":"For this fish, it's actually whole cells"},{"time":664000,"text":"with nuclei and membranes."},{"time":666000,"text":"It's energetically very costly for this fish to do this,"},{"time":668000,"text":"and we have no idea why it does it --"},{"time":671000,"text":"another one of these great mysteries that needs to be solved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676000,"text":"Now, another form of defense"},{"time":678000,"text":"is something called a burglar alarm --"},{"time":680000,"text":"same reason you have a burglar alarm on your car;"},{"time":682000,"text":"the honking horn and flashing lights"},{"time":684000,"text":"are meant to attract the attention of, hopefully,"},{"time":686000,"text":"the police that will come and take the burglar away --"},{"time":688000,"text":"when an animal's caught in the clutches of a predator,"},{"time":690000,"text":"its only hope for escape may be"},{"time":692000,"text":"to attract the attention of something bigger and nastier"},{"time":694000,"text":"that will attack their attacker,"},{"time":696000,"text":"thereby affording them a chance for escape."},{"time":699000,"text":"This jellyfish, for example, has"},{"time":701000,"text":"a spectacular bioluminescent display."},{"time":703000,"text":"This is us chasing it in the submersible."},{"time":705000,"text":"That's not luminescence, that's reflected light from the gonads."},{"time":708000,"text":"We capture it in a very special device on the front of the submersible"},{"time":711000,"text":"that allows us to bring it up in really pristine condition,"},{"time":714000,"text":"bring it into the lab on the ship."},{"time":716000,"text":"And then to generate the display you're about to see,"},{"time":718000,"text":"all I did was touch it once per second"},{"time":720000,"text":"on its nerve ring with a sharp pick"},{"time":722000,"text":"that's sort of like the sharp tooth of a fish."},{"time":724000,"text":"And once this display gets going, I'm not touching it anymore."},{"time":727000,"text":"This is an unbelievable light show."},{"time":730000,"text":"It's this pinwheel of light,"},{"time":732000,"text":"and I've done calculations that show that this could be seen"},{"time":734000,"text":"from as much as 300 feet away by a predator."},{"time":737000,"text":"And I thought, \"You know,"},{"time":739000,"text":"that might actually make a pretty good lure.\""},{"time":741000,"text":"Because one of the things that's frustrated me"},{"time":744000,"text":"as a deep-sea explorer"},{"time":746000,"text":"is how many animals there probably are in the ocean that we know nothing about"},{"time":749000,"text":"because of the way we explore the ocean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752000,"text":"The primary way that we know about what lives in the ocean"},{"time":755000,"text":"is we go out and drag nets behind ships."},{"time":758000,"text":"And I defy you to name any other branch of science"},{"time":760000,"text":"that still depends on hundreds of year-old technology."},{"time":763000,"text":"The other primary way is we go down"},{"time":765000,"text":"with submersibles and remote-operated vehicles."},{"time":767000,"text":"I've made hundreds of dives in submersibles."},{"time":770000,"text":"When I'm sitting in a submersible though,"},{"time":772000,"text":"I know that I'm not unobtrusive at all --"},{"time":775000,"text":"I've got bright lights and noisy thrusters --"},{"time":777000,"text":"any animal with any sense is going to be long gone."},{"time":780000,"text":"So, I've wanted for a long time"},{"time":783000,"text":"to figure out a different way to explore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785000,"text":"And so, sometime ago, I got this idea for a camera system."},{"time":788000,"text":"It's not exactly rocket science. We call this thing Eye-in-the-Sea."},{"time":791000,"text":"And scientists have done this on land for years;"},{"time":793000,"text":"we just use a color that the animals can't see"},{"time":796000,"text":"and then a camera that can see that color."},{"time":798000,"text":"You can't use infrared in the sea."},{"time":800000,"text":"We use far-red light, but even that's a problem"},{"time":802000,"text":"because it gets absorbed so quickly."},{"time":804000,"text":"Made an intensified camera,"},{"time":806000,"text":"wanted to make this electronic jellyfish."},{"time":808000,"text":"Thing is, in science,"},{"time":811000,"text":"you basically have to tell the funding agencies what you're going to discover"},{"time":814000,"text":"before they'll give you the money."},{"time":816000,"text":"And I didn't know what I was going to discover,"},{"time":818000,"text":"so I couldn't get the funding for this."},{"time":820000,"text":"So I kluged this together, I got the Harvey Mudd Engineering Clinic"},{"time":823000,"text":"to actually do it as an undergraduate student project initially,"},{"time":826000,"text":"and then I kluged funding from a whole bunch of different sources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829000,"text":"Monterey Bay Aquarium Research Institute"},{"time":831000,"text":"gave me time with their ROV"},{"time":834000,"text":"so that I could test it and we could figure out,"},{"time":836000,"text":"you know, for example, which colors of red light we had to use"},{"time":839000,"text":"so that we could see the animals, but they couldn't see us --"},{"time":842000,"text":"get the electronic jellyfish working."},{"time":845000,"text":"And you can see just what a shoestring operation this really was,"},{"time":848000,"text":"because we cast these 16 blue LEDs in epoxy"},{"time":851000,"text":"and you can see in the epoxy mold that we used,"},{"time":853000,"text":"the word Ziploc is still visible."},{"time":856000,"text":"Needless to say, when it's kluged together like this,"},{"time":859000,"text":"there were a lot of trials and tribulations getting this working."},{"time":862000,"text":"But there came a moment when it all came together,"},{"time":864000,"text":"and everything worked."},{"time":866000,"text":"And, remarkably, that moment got caught on film"},{"time":868000,"text":"by photographer Mark Richards,"},{"time":870000,"text":"who happened to be there at the precise moment"},{"time":872000,"text":"that we discovered that it all came together."},{"time":875000,"text":"That's me on the left,"},{"time":877000,"text":"my graduate student at the time, Erika Raymond,"},{"time":879000,"text":"and Lee Fry, who was the engineer on the project."},{"time":882000,"text":"And we have this photograph posted in our lab in a place of honor"},{"time":885000,"text":"with the caption: \"Engineer satisfying two women at once.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":889000,"text":"And we were very, very happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891000,"text":"So now we had a system"},{"time":893000,"text":"that we could actually take to some place"},{"time":895000,"text":"that was kind of like an oasis on the bottom of the ocean"},{"time":897000,"text":"that might be patrolled by large predators."},{"time":901000,"text":"And so, the place that we took it to"},{"time":903000,"text":"was this place called a Brine Pool,"},{"time":905000,"text":"which is in the northern part of the Gulf of Mexico."},{"time":907000,"text":"It's a magical place."},{"time":909000,"text":"And I know this footage isn't going to look like anything to you --"},{"time":911000,"text":"we had a crummy camera at the time --"},{"time":913000,"text":"but I was ecstatic."},{"time":915000,"text":"We're at the edge of the Brine Pool,"},{"time":917000,"text":"there's a fish that's swimming towards the camera."},{"time":920000,"text":"It's clearly undisturbed by us."},{"time":922000,"text":"And I had my window into the deep sea."},{"time":925000,"text":"I, for the first time, could see what animals were doing down there"},{"time":928000,"text":"when we weren't down there disturbing them in some way."},{"time":932000,"text":"Four hours into the deployment,"},{"time":934000,"text":"we had programmed the electronic jellyfish"},{"time":936000,"text":"to come on for the first time."},{"time":938000,"text":"Eighty-six seconds after"},{"time":940000,"text":"it went into its pinwheel display,"},{"time":942000,"text":"we recorded this:"},{"time":945000,"text":"This is a squid, over six feet long,"},{"time":947000,"text":"that is so new to science,"},{"time":949000,"text":"it cannot be placed in any known scientific family."},{"time":953000,"text":"I could not have asked for a better proof of concept."}]},{"cues":[{"time":956000,"text":"And based on this, I went back to the National Science Foundation"},{"time":958000,"text":"and said, \"This is what we will discover.\""},{"time":961000,"text":"And they gave me enough money to do it right,"},{"time":963000,"text":"which has involved developing the world's first deep-sea webcam --"},{"time":966000,"text":"which has been installed in"},{"time":968000,"text":"the Monterey Canyon for the past year --"},{"time":970000,"text":"and now, more recently,"},{"time":972000,"text":"a modular form of this system,"},{"time":974000,"text":"a much more mobile form"},{"time":976000,"text":"that's a lot easier to launch and recover,"},{"time":978000,"text":"that I hope can be used on Sylvia's \"hope spots\""},{"time":981000,"text":"to help explore"},{"time":983000,"text":"and protect these areas,"},{"time":985000,"text":"and, for me, learn more about"},{"time":987000,"text":"the bioluminescence in these \"hope spots.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":990000,"text":"So one of these take-home messages here"},{"time":993000,"text":"is, there is still a lot to explore in the oceans."},{"time":996000,"text":"And Sylvia has said"},{"time":998000,"text":"that we are destroying the oceans before we even know what's in them,"},{"time":1001000,"text":"and she's right."},{"time":1003000,"text":"So if you ever, ever get an opportunity"},{"time":1005000,"text":"to take a dive in a submersible,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"say yes -- a thousand times, yes --"},{"time":1010000,"text":"and please turn out the lights."},{"time":1012000,"text":"I promise, you'll love it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1014000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1016000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}